qas.question: Who is in charge of the day to day operation of the CIA?
What is the title of the person who manages the relationship between the CIA and the Unified Combatant Commands?

answers.text: The Associate Director of military affairs

qas.question: What three ways does the Executive office support the U.S. military?

answers.text: providing it with information it gathers, receiving information from military intelligence organizations, and cooperating on field activities

context: The Executive Office also supports the U.S. military by <a2_0>providing it with information it gathers, receiving information from military intelligence organizations, and cooperating on field activities<a2_0/>. <a0_0>The Executive Director<a0_0/> is in charge of the day to day operation of the CIA, and each branch of the service has its own Director. <a1_0>The Associate Director of military affairs<a1_0/>, a senior military officer, manages the relationship between the CIA and the Unified Combatant Commands, who produce regional/operational intelligence and consume national intelligence.
